                "data": {
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "type": "Words",
                      "data": {
                        "value": "The type of blending used to combine the colormapped data values with the illumination intensity.  For backwards compatibility, this defaults to \"hsv\". Note that for most topographic surfaces, \"overlay\" or \"soft\" appear more visually realistic. If a user-defined function is supplied, it is expected to combine an MxNx3 RGB array of floats (ranging 0 to 1) with an MxNx1 hillshade array (also 0 to 1).  (Call signature "
                      }
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "Verbatim",
